Napoli extended their lead at the top of Serie A to 16 points after deserving 3-0 victory over bottom-of-the-table Cremonese. Goals from Khvicha Kvaratskhelia, Victor Osimhen and Eljif Elmas gave Napoli their 19th win of the season. The Naples club, chasing their first Italian title since 1990, have now won six matches in a row and have dropped just seven points this season. READ MORE: Osimhen Named Serie A Player Of The Month For January Second-placed Inter Milan can reduce Napoli’s lead when they play Sampdoria on Monday. Earlier in the day, Adrien Rabiot’s goal gave Juventus a 1-0 win over Fiorentina.